<TITLE> Over 2,000 schools score 100% pass rate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 26 (bdnews24.com)  The number of educational institutions with 100 percent of students passing the SSC and equivalent exams for 2008 has increased to 2,272. The number of institutions with a zero pass rate is 91, education adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman told a press conference on the publication of SSC and equivalent exam results under nine education boards Thursday. Of the 2,272 institutions, 484 are schools, 1770 madrasas and 18 technical institutions. The number of institutions having 100 percent successful students was 774 in 2007. As many as 185 successful schools out of 484 are under Dhaka board, 71 under Rajshahi, 72 under Comilla, 58 under Jessore, 31 under Chittagong, 57 under Barisal and 10 under Sylhet board. None of the examinees from 34 schools, 40 madrasas and 17 technical institutions passed the hurdle. Of 34 worst-performing schools, six are under Dhaka board, eight under Rajshahi, four under Jessore, two under Chittagong, 11 under Barisal and three under Sylhet. bdn
